def hist_gen(df, column, colours, bins_val=5):
    
    assert type(colours) is list, 'Not a list'
    assert type(df).__name__ == 'DataFrame', 'Please use pandas DataFrame structure'
    assert type(column) is str, 'Column name not given'

    
    plt.figure(figsize=(20,10))
    plt.grid(False)
    n, bins, patches = plt.hist(df[column], bins=bins_val)
    
    if len(colours) < len(patches):
        print('Warning: There should be the same number of colours as bars if more colours are needed')
        x = -(-len(patches)//len(colours)) # round always rounds down and so does //, therefore using
        # a negative value will always round up
        colours = colours*x
    
    for i in range(len(patches)):
        c = colours[i]
        patches[i].set_fc(c)
    
    #plt.ylim(max(df[column].value_counts()) + (max(df[column].value_counts()*0.4)))
    plt.xlabel(f'{column} concentration')
    plt.ylabel(f'No. of Patients with similar {column}')
    plt.title(f'Distribution of {column}')
    plt.savefig(f'./Distribution of {column}.png')

def linearity_check(features, columns,save=False):
    name = ''
    for x in columns[0]:
        if x != '_':
            name += x
        else:
            break
    if save:
        for i in range(0,len(features)):
            plt.title('Treg concentrations over time')
            plt.xlabel('Conc (g/L)')
            plt.ylabel('Times')
            plt.plot(['Basal','48h','72h'], [np.array(features[columns[0]])[i], np.array(features[columns[1]])[i], 
                           np.array(features[columns[2]])[i]], '-o')

            plt.savefig(f'./Treg concentrations over time for case {str(i+1)}')
            plt.show()
    else:
        for i in range(0,len(features)):
            plt.title('Treg concentrations over time')
            plt.xlabel('Conc (g/L)')
            plt.ylabel('Times')
            plt.plot(['Basal','48h','72h'], [np.array(features[columns[0]])[i], np.array(features[columns[1]])[i], 
                               np.array(features[columns[2]])[i]], '-o')
            plt.show()

def extrapolator(features, j, k):
    for i in range(0,len(features)):
        if np.isnan(features.iloc[i,j-1]) == True:
            features.iloc[i,j-1] = 0
        if np.isnan(features.iloc[i,k-1]) == True:
            features.iloc[i,k-1] = 0
            
        if np.isnan(features.iloc[i,j+1]) == True:
            features.iloc[i,j+1] = (((features.iloc[i,j] + features.iloc[i,j-1])/2) + features.iloc[i,j])
        else:
            if np.isnan(features.iloc[i,j]) == True:
                features.iloc[i,j] = (features.iloc[i,j-1] + features.iloc[i,j+1])/2

        if np.isnan(features.iloc[i,k+1]) == True:
            features.iloc[i,k+1] = (((features.iloc[i,k] + features.iloc[i,k-1])/2) + features.iloc[i,k])
        else:
            if np.isnan(features.iloc[i,k]) == True:
                features.iloc[i,k] = (features.iloc[i,k-1] + features.iloc[i,k+1])/2
    return features
